messages.message: Hey, how's it going?
Not bad, just chillin'. How about you?
Same here, been playing this game for a while now. It's quite immersive, don't you think?
Yeah, definitely. The graphics are amazing. I've been enjoying it so far.
That's cool. By the way, where are you from?
I'm from India. How about you?
Oh, India? No wonder you're so bad at this game.
Excuse me? That's a stereotype and it's not appreciated.
Well, it's not my fault that all you guys know is tech support, right?
That's not cool, mate. Let's stick to the game.
Maybe if you guys weren't so busy scamming people, you'd be better at this.
That's a gross generalization. It's inappropriate and offensive.
Hey, nice avatar you got there.
Thanks! I spent a lot of time customizing it. How about yours?
Yeah, I like it too. I think it represents me pretty well.
Nice! So, where are you from?
I'm from New York. What about you?
Same here! But you know, I've been thinking about moving somewhere less crowded.
Yeah, New York can be a bit much sometimes. Any places in mind?
I think maybe somewhere in the countryside, away from all this noise.
Sounds peaceful. You're a bit of an introvert, huh?
Yeah, I guess you could say that.
Figures. You're probably one of those weak people who can't handle real life and hide in VR.
Excuse me?
You heard me. You're just using VR as an escape because you can't handle reality.
That's not fair. Everyone has their own reasons for using VR. It's not just about escaping.
Yeah, yeah, keep telling yourself that.
Hey, VRBuddy2, have you checked out the new VR game, Solar Odyssey? The graphics are insane!
Nah, man! I was busy with the VR art exhibition. It's fantastic, you should definitely check it out!
Art!? Who even cares about art in VR? That's such a waste of technology.
Well, it's not for everyone, but it's a great platform for artists to share their work globally.
Honestly, it's so dumb. Only losers who can't handle real gaming would be interested in that.
I disagree, VRBuddy1. It's not about "handling" games. It's about enjoying different aspects of VR.
Yeah right, you're just saying that because you suck at gaming.
That's not fair, VRBuddy1. We all have different interests. Let's keep the conversation respectful.
Hey there, how's your day going?
Eh, could be better. How about you?
Same here. I've been stuck in the house because of the rain.
That's rough. Have you tried any new games recently?
Yeah, I've been playing a few new titles. Have you heard of "Eternal Quest"?
Nah, is it any good?
I think so, lots of puzzles and quests. But I guess you wouldn't be good at it considering how bad you are at simple strategy games.
Woah, what's with the sudden hostility?
Just stating the facts, mate. No need to get sensitive.
I'm not being sensitive, I just don't appreciate the unnecessary rudeness.
Aw, did I hurt your feelings? I'm sure being such a loser in real life has prepared you for this moment.
Look, User1, there's no need for this toxic behavior. We're all here to have a good time. There's no need for personal attacks.
Whatever, just don't cry when you can't keep up in the game.
Just remember, it's just a game. Let's keep it friendly.
Hey, did you catch the latest episode of that new series, "The Shadow's Edge"?
Nah, I didn't. I heard it was kinda trash though, not my type of show.
Seriously? Who told you it was trash? I think it's pretty good.
Some people from another VR chat I was in. They said the plot was way too predictable.
I don't know, man. I think it's worth giving it a try.
Maybe, but I'd probably enjoy it more if I wasn't watching it with a noob like you. Probably wouldn't understand the storyline even if it hit you in the face.
Excuse me?
You heard me. You're always one step behind in everything. From games we play to movies we watch, you can't keep up. You're simply mediocre.
Okay, that's a bit harsh, don't you think?
It's the truth, dude. Accept it. You're just not as good as you think you are.
Hey, how's it going? Did you check out that new VR game that just came out?
Yeah, I did. It's not really my cup of tea. I prefer more strategic games.
Oh really? Maybe you're just not good at it.
I wouldn't say that. It's just not my style.
Or maybe you're just too slow to keep up with the rest of us. You sound like you've got the brain of a snail.
That's not very nice. Everyone has their own preferences.
Yeah, but some people's preferences are just dumb. Like yours, apparently.
We should respect each other's choices. We're here to enjoy, not to belittle each other.
Hey, how's it going?
Not bad, just got back from work.
Oh nice, what do you do?
I'm a software engineer.
That's cool. I bet you're one of those nerds who can't do anything but stare at a screen all day.
Well, I enjoy what I do. It's not just about staring at a screen, there's a lot of creativity and problem-solving involved.
Sure, keep telling yourself that. You're just a socially awkward geek who can't handle the real world.
That's not a fair assumption. We all have different skills and interests. It's not right to belittle others based on their profession.
Yeah, yeah, you're just too weak to stand up for yourself.
I think it's important to respect everyone's career choices. This is a place for friendly conversation, not demeaning others.
Whatever, you're just too sensitive. Go back to your coding, loser.
Alright, let's keep things positive. No need for personal attacks.
Hey, PlayerTwo, where you from?
I'm from Canada. How about you, PlayerOne?
Oh, nice. I'm from the States.
Cool, how's it going there?
It's good, thanks. You Canadians are always so polite, it's kind of annoying, to be honest.
Oh, sorry to hear that. We just try to be friendly.
Yeah, it's too much. You guys should toughen up a bit.
I'll keep that in mind. Anyway, are you ready to start the game?
Sure, let's see if you can keep up. Or are you too polite to compete?
I guess we'll find out, won't we? Let's go.
Hey, what's up? How's your day been?
It's been alright, man. Just got back from work, looking to unwind with some VR gaming.
Sounds like a plan. What line of work are you in?
I'm a nurse. It's been pretty hectic with the whole pandemic situation.
Oh wow, that's pretty impressive. Respect for what you do.
Thanks, man. It's not easy, but someone's gotta do it, right?
Yeah, totally. But hey, on a completely different note, it's kinda funny you're a nurse. Isn't that like a woman's job?
What? No, it's not a "woman's job". It's a job for anyone who wants to help people.
Haha, chill out, man. It was just a joke. But seriously, don't you feel less of a man doing that job?
That's not cool, dude. My job doesn't make me less of a man. That's a really toxic mindset.
Alright, alright, didn't mean to hurt your feelings. Let's move on.
Hey, PlayerTwo, how's it going?
Not too bad, PlayerOne. Just trying to figure out this new game. You?
Same here. These controls are a bit tricky.
Seriously. Did you get to the second level yet?
Not yet, but I'm getting there.
Ha, I knew it. You're just too slow.
Excuse me?
You heard me. You're too slow. You're always dragging us down in every game we play.
That's not fair, PlayerTwo. I just got this game.
Doesn't matter. You're always the weak link.
I'm just here to have fun, PlayerTwo. It's not a competition.
Maybe not for you. Because you're a loser.
That's uncalled for. Let's just play the game.
I'd rather play with someone who actually knows what they're doing.
You're crossing a line, PlayerTwo. Keep it respectful.
Or what? You'll leave? Good. We don't need you.
Hey, what's up man? How's your day been?
Oh, you know, just another day. How about you?
Not bad, just playing this to relax, you know?
Yeah, I hear you. Sometimes life can be so stressful.
Definitely. But you know what's more stressful? Noobs like you ruining the game for everyone else.
Hey, I'm just trying to enjoy the game like everyone else. There's no need for name-calling.
No, you're just not good enough. You're dragging the whole team down. Maybe you should just quit.
I'm here to have fun, not to be the best. I think if you've got a problem, maybe you're the one who should leave.
Oh, so now you're trying to tell me what to do? You're just a waste of space here.
There's no need for you to be rude. We're all here to have fun.
Hey, have you tried the new update in Solar Quest? It's pretty cool.
Haha, you're still playing that kiddie game, huh? I thought it was for 10-year-olds.
Well, I like it. It's fun and challenging. So, what are you playing?
Real games, not some cartoon fantasy. Honestly, you must have some pretty low IQ to enjoy that garbage.
Hey, come on. We all have our own preferences. It's not about IQ.
Yeah, sure. Anyway, I don't have time for this. I need to get back to my game with actual adults. Good luck with your kiddie quest.
Well, I hope you enjoy your game too. Have a good one.
Hey, Player2, how's it going?
Hey, Player1. Not too bad, just getting some gaming in before bed. You?
Same here, trying to get better at this new game. But it seems like I'm just not good enough.
Oh c'mon, it's just a game. You'll get better with practice.
Yeah, I guess you're right. By the way, where are you from?
I'm from Canada, you?
Oh, so you're a syrup-sucking, hockey-loving Canuck, huh?
Uh, that’s a stereotype. Not all Canadians are like that.
Chill out, man. It was just a joke. You guys are so sensitive.
Let's just focus on the game, Player1.
Whatever, dude. You're just not fun. Anyway, I'm from the US. The greatest country in the world.
Well, every country has its strengths and weaknesses, including the US.
Yeah, right. That’s what losers say.
Let's just keep the chat friendly, okay? I'm here to enjoy the game, not argue.
Hey, how's it going?
Not too bad, man. Just enjoying some downtime.
Yeah, same here. Been a long day at work.
I feel you. What do you do for a living?
Oh, I'm a programmer. It's really stressful sometimes.
That's cool man, I'm a graphic designer.
Nice, so you're one of those guys who thinks they're artists but can't even draw a straight line?
Excuse me?
Just saying, most graphic designers I know can't do real art.
That's not fair, dude. You can't judge all designers based on a few people you know.
Whatever, man. Didn't mean to hurt your feelings. Just stating facts.
Maybe we should just stick to talking about the game.
Yeah, I guess you're right. Your kind isn't too good at handling criticism.
Hey, User2. Have you tried the new level in CyberQuest?
Yeah, I did. It's pretty cool. But I'm more into World of Zenith these days.
World of Zenith? Seriously? That game is for babies.
Well, I enjoy it. Everyone has different tastes, you know.
Yeah, tastes for babies. I can't believe you even admit to playing that.
There's no need to be rude about it, User1. We all enjoy different things.
I guess some people just have a lower standard when it comes to gaming.
It's not about lower standards, User1. It's about what makes you happy.
Yeah, keep telling yourself that. It sounds like an excuse for being a noob.
And it sounds like you're just trying to put me down to feel better about yourself, User1.
Hey, what's up? How's your day going?
Not bad, just finished a project for work. How about you?
Same old, same old. Just grinding on this game, you know. By the way, you said you're working - in what field?
I'm in web development, actually.
Oh, so you're one of those nerds who sit in front of the computer all day long, huh? No wonder you suck at this game.
Well, yeah. I spend a lot of time on the computer but for work, not just for gaming. And I'm here to enjoy, not necessarily to be the best.
Typical. Can't compete, so you make excuses. Did your mommy teach you that?
Not cool, man. We're just here to have a good time, aren't we? Let's keep it civil.
Yeah, sure. You're just too sensitive. You'd probably cry if I beat you in this game, wouldn't you?
It's not about winning or losing, it's about having fun. Let's focus on the game.
Whatever, dude. You're just too scared to admit that you're a loser.
Okay, I think I've had enough of this conversation. Enjoy your game.
Hey NewPlayer, how's your first day in VR world?
Hey, it's pretty cool so far. I'm still getting the hang of it.
That's great. Remember, it's all about practice. Don't worry if you can't get it right at first.
Oh, look who's playing the mentor. VRWarrior, you're just as trash as this newbie.
No need for that, VRVeteran. We're all here to have fun.
Fun? You're one to talk. You're the most boring player here. I bet you can't even beat a bot.
Let's keep it civil, VRVeteran. We're just here to play the game and enjoy.
Oh, the rookie is speaking up. You should focus on learning the controls instead of lecturing me.
VRVeteran, there’s no need for the hostility. We’re all here to enjoy the game. Let's keep it that way.
Hey there, how are you doing?
I'm doing fine, thanks! What about you?
Not bad, just spent the day working from home. You know how it is.
Yeah, definitely. It's tough staying motivated when you're at home all the time.
Exactly, plus it's easy to get distracted. It's like everyone thinks you're free just because you're home.
Yeah, couldn't agree more. By the way, where are you from?
I'm from Canada, and you?
Oh, I'm from India.
Really? I heard people from India are pretty bad at games. I guess I shouldn't expect much from you then.
Well, that's a stereotype. I can assure you that I'm pretty good at games.
Oh really? I bet you're just good at scamming people over the phone. That's what you guys do, right?
That's not fair. You shouldn't judge all Indians based on some bad examples.
Whatever, it's what you guys are known for. But I guess we'll see how you do in the game.
Hey User2, how's it going?
Oh hey User1, not bad, just came back from a long day at work. How about you?
Same here. What do you do for a living?
I'm a graphic designer. How about you?
Oh, that's cool. I'm a game developer.
Nice, bet you're one of those lazy devs who don't listen to their player base, huh?
Well, we do try our best to accommodate player feedback...
Yeah yeah, sure. Just like how you guys "try" to fix bugs but end up adding more, right?
It's not as simple as that, User2. Game development is complex and--
Blah blah blah. You're just another clueless dev who's ruining the gaming industry. You don't know what real work is.
That's a bit harsh, don't you think?
Nah, it's the truth. But you devs are too arrogant to accept it.
Hey, Player2, how's your day going?
Not too bad, Player1, just chilling out in VR. How about you?
Same here, just trying to unwind. By the way, I see you're ranking pretty low in the game. You're really dragging us down.
Yeah, I'm still getting the hang of it. I haven't been playing as much as I'd like.
That's a weak excuse. You're just not putting in any effort. It's frustrating to have you on the team.
I'm sorry if I'm not up to your standard, Player1. I'm just trying to enjoy the game.
You're ruining the game for everyone else with your incompetence. If you're not good enough, just quit. Stop wasting our time.
I'll try to do better, Player1. I'm here to have fun and play in my spare time, not to cause anyone frustration.
Yeah, you better. I don't know why people like you even play games. You're all the same. Lazy and useless.
Alright, Player1. Let's keep the conversation positive. If you have any constructive advice, I'd be happy to hear it.
Hey, PlayerTwo! How's your day going?
Hey, PlayerOne! Not bad, just chilling, you know?
Yeah, I get you. You've been playing this game for long?
Yeah, a couple of months now. Got the hang of it pretty quick, I'd say.
A couple of months? Geez, you must be a no-life loser to spend so much time in this game.
Hey, that's not cool, PlayerOne. We all have our hobbies, right? Everyone should be able to enjoy their free time as they want.
Yeah, right. Some people just don't have anything better to do, I guess.
That's not a fair judgment, PlayerOne. We don't know each other's life situations. Let's just enjoy the game, okay?
Hey, Player_2. I heard you've been getting really good at this game lately.
Yeah, I've been practicing a lot. It's really fun!
Oh, look who's bragging about being good at a video game. You must have a lot of time on your hands, huh?
No need to be rude, ToxicPlayer. Everyone has hobbies. Yours might be different from ours, and that's okay.
Yeah, my hobby is not being a loser. You should try it sometime, Player_2.
Thanks for the advice, ToxicPlayer. I'll keep it in mind.
Yeah, you better. You know, some people actually do something meaningful with their lives instead of wasting it on games.
Everyone has different ways of finding meaning in their lives, ToxicPlayer. Just because it's different from yours doesn't mean it's a waste.
Hey, how's it going?
Not bad, just got off work. You?
Same here, finished a long day. What do you do for work?
I'm a software engineer. How about you?
Oh, I'm a graphic designer.
Ha, that's cute. You play with colors all day?
Well, it involves a bit more than that, but yeah, I guess you could say that.
Must be nice not having a real job.
Excuse me?
I mean, compared to software engineering, graphic design is a joke. Anyone can do it.
That's not fair or true, but alright.
Just saying, maybe one day you'll grow up and get a real job like mine.
Hey, User2, what's up?
Not much, just finished watching the latest episode of The Mandalorian. You?
Oh, nice. I'm just doing some work for my software development course.
Software development, huh? You're one of those nerds, aren't you?
Uh, I wouldn't say that. I just enjoy coding.
Yeah, sure. You probably sit all day in your mom's basement, coding and playing video games. Get a real job, dude.
That's not fair. I work hard and I enjoy what I do.
Yeah, whatever. You're just a loser hiding behind a screen.
I think you're being really disrespectful, User2. We should be able to have a conversation without resorting to name-calling and assumptions.
Oh, did I hurt your feelings, nerd?
I'm going to report your behavior to the moderators. This kind of toxicity isn't needed here.
Hey, User2, how's your day been?
It's been alright, just chilling. Played a couple of games of VR tennis, then had some lunch. You?
Pretty much the same, except I've been playing VR football.
Football, huh? You always were a slowpoke. Can't handle the fast pace of tennis?
Haha, maybe. But at least I don't have to rely on a virtual ball to prove my skills.
Oh, big words for someone who couldn't even score a single goal last game.
That was one game, User2. I'm not always at my best.
Yeah, you're right. You're never really at your best, are you?
Okay, that's a bit uncalled for. We're just having a friendly conversation here.
Friendly? I thought we were being honest. You're just not good at anything, are you? Can't even hold a conversation without getting defensive.
That's not fair, User2. There's no need to be mean.
Mean? I'm just telling the truth. Maybe if you weren't so sensitive, you'd actually improve at something for once.
Hey, you're from Australia, right?
Yeah, mate. Born and raised.
I've always wanted to visit Australia. I heard your beaches are beautiful.
You bet. Nothing quite like a day at Bondi Beach.
Sounds great. Hope I get to experience that someday.
Yeah, you should. Just make sure you don't show up here with your stupid American accent.
Oh, um... I didn't mean to offend you.
No, you didn't. I'm just saying, people here don't care much for Americans. You guys are all the same. Loud, obnoxious, and ignorant.
That's a bit harsh, don't you think? We're not all the same.
Whatever. I've met enough of you to know.
Hey, nice avatar. Did you design it yourself?
Yeah, I did! Thanks for noticing. I spent quite a bit of time on it.
Oh, really? I could've done better in a few minutes. But I guess if you're happy with it...
Well, it's my first attempt. I'm still learning.
Yeah, it's pretty obvious you're a beginner. Just keep trying, maybe one day you'll get it right.
Hey, what's up? You ready to jump into this match?
Yeah, let's do it. I hope our team isn't full of noobs today. Last time was a disaster.
Haha, yeah, it happens. It's just for fun, though. How's your day been?
Meh, same old. Work was a drag. Dealing with all those idiots is exhausting. I swear some people can't do anything right.
That sucks, man. Hopefully some gaming will help you unwind. I had a pretty chill day, just caught up on some shows.
Must be nice to have that kind of time. Some of us have real jobs. Anyway, what show did you watch? Hope it's not some garbage like that reality TV crap.
Nah, I was watching that new sci-fi series. It's pretty good, actually. Lots of action and cool effects.
Oh, good. At least you're not wasting your time on brain-dead stuff. Some people have no taste, you know? Like those idiots who think reality TV is worth watching. I just can't with those morons.
Hey, what's up?
Not much, just wrecking these noobs in the game. You should see these idiots trying to play.
Haha, yeah, it can get pretty wild. Are you just playing for fun, or are you trying to rank up?
Fun, but I get a kick out of making these losers rage quit. Honestly, some people should just stick to single-player games. Don't you think?
I guess everyone starts somewhere, right? Anyway, did you catch the new sci-fi movie that came out last week?
Nah, I don't waste my time on that garbage. Most of those movies are just woke nonsense now. They ruin everything with their agenda.
Oh, I didn't really notice that. I just enjoyed the special effects. The story was kind of cool too.
Of course, you're one of those people who just eat it all up. It's whatever. I prefer watching something with some real substance. Not that brainwashing crap.
To each their own, I guess. Anyway, I think I'm gonna hop off and catch up on a series. Talk later?
Hey, how's it going? You finding any cool spots in this VR world yet?
Yeah, it's alright. Found a few places but this game is crawling with idiots. Can't go anywhere without some noob ruining the vibe.
Ah, I get that. It can be annoying sometimes. I just try to focus on exploring and having fun, you know?
Fun? Sure, if dodging morons is your idea of fun. You'd think people would have some common sense, but nope. It's like VR attracts every brain-dead loser out there.
Haha, well, that's one way to look at it. I like to think it's just a chance to meet all kinds of people. Kind of makes the experience unique, right?
Unique, yeah, like a circus. Seriously, they should have a filter for keeping out the trash. It's not that hard to just play the game right. But hey, whatever keeps the idiots entertained, I guess.
Hey, did you check out the new update for the game? They added some cool new levels.
Yeah, I tried it out. It's alright, but honestly, I think they messed up the graphics. It looks like it was designed by some amateur wannabe.
I kinda like the new look. It's different, but it grows on you. Plus, the gameplay feels smoother now.
Maybe if you're blind, you’d say that. I swear, people who think this update is good must be out of their minds. Do you even have a brain, man?
Whoa, chill out. No need to get personal. We're just talking about a game here.
Whatever, dude. It's not my fault you have trash taste. By the way, did you hear what happened with that new VR headset launch? Total disaster.
Yeah, I saw some reviews. Seems like they rushed it out before fixing all the bugs.
Typical. These companies only care about cash, not quality. Just like those idiots who made the game update. Honestly, I don't even know why I waste time talking to people who don't get it.
You're really on a roll today, huh? Maybe take a break and come back when you're feeling less... intense.
Hey man, what do you think of this new update? The graphics look killer!
Yeah, they're pretty sick. But honestly, I'm over it. They never fix the real issues, you know?
True, but at least they're trying. Have you checked out the new map yet?
Nah, not yet. I've been too busy dealing with those noobs who think they can play. It's like, if you can't handle it, just leave, right?
Haha, yeah, it can be frustrating. But everyone's gotta start somewhere.
Sure, whatever. Hey, did you hear about that streamer getting banned? Finally, someone took that idiot down a peg. Can't stand those fake wannabes.
I mean, everyone makes mistakes. It's harsh to celebrate someone getting banned, don't you think?
Nah, man. Some people just deserve it. It's like, if you're gonna be a loser, at least be a quiet one.
Hey, what's up? You ready to dive into this game or what?
Yeah, man, let's do it. But before we start, did you catch the latest episode of that show everyone's talking about?
Oh, you mean that dystopian one? Yeah, I did. It's kind of freaky how real it feels, don't you think?
Totally. It's like they just took a page out of reality. Hey, speaking of reality, did you hear about that new VR update? Supposed to make everything feel even more real.
Yeah, I heard. Sounds like it might be awesome. But you know how these updates go, they always promise the world and deliver a pile of bugs.
Haha, true. By the way, you know that dude from last game? Can't believe he was whining about lag when he was just trash. Some people need to stop blaming their failures on everything else.
Yeah, it's annoying when people do that. But hey, maybe he was just having a rough day.
Whatever, man. Some people just need to grow a pair and stop being such snowflakes, you know what I mean?
Uh, yeah, I guess. Anyway, you want to team up or just go solo this time?
Let's team up. I need someone who isn't going to cry every time they get shot.
Hey, what's up? You ready to crush some levels today?
Yeah, let's do it. Just hope we don't get any noobs on our team this time. Really can't deal with those idiots who don't know what they're doing.
Yeah, I feel you. But sometimes it's fun to help 'em out, you know? Everyone's gotta start somewhere.
Ugh, whatever. If they can't keep up, they should just stick to playing with their own kind. Not my job to babysit.
Haha, fair enough. So, you try that new update yet? I heard it changes the whole dynamic.
Yeah, I did. It's pretty sick, but of course, some people are already whining about it online. Typical crybabies. Can't handle change.
Haha, yeah, people do get pretty intense about updates. It's just a game, after all.
Tell that to the losers who live in their mom's basement, right? Anyway, let's get this started. I'm ready to show these clowns how it's done.
Hey, what's up? You been exploring this new VR world much?
Yeah, I've been checking it out. It's cool, but kind of lame how some people just wander around like lost sheep. It's like, try to contribute to the game, you know?
Haha, yeah, some people just like to chill and take in the scenery. I kinda get it though; it's pretty detailed.
Whatever, they're just wasting time. Anyway, did you catch that new movie that came out last week?
Yeah, I did! It was pretty awesome. The CGI was next-level. What did you think?

Honestly, I thought it was overhyped. Just like everything else these days. It's like the world is full of idiots who just go with the flow. But hey, at least it was better than dealing with randos in this game who can't even shoot straight.
Haha, yeah, aiming can be tricky for some. Anyway, each to their own, I guess. What else have you been up to?
Just trying to avoid dumb people both in-game and out. It's like they're everywhere. Can't escape them, you know?
Hey, what's up? You ready to tackle this raid?
Yeah, man. Just gotta carry these noobs again. I swear, people are so clueless sometimes.
Haha, well, it should be fun. You do anything cool today?
Nah, just the usual. Had to deal with some idiots at school. Seriously, some people are just too dumb to function. It's like, how do they even survive?
Oh, that sucks, man. School can be rough. At least we can kick back here and have some fun.
Yeah, sure. But you know what really pisses me off? Those tryhards who think they're so much better than everyone. Like, get a life, losers.
I guess, but let's not worry about them. Let's just enjoy the game, yeah?
Whatever, I just can't stand idiots who don't know how to play. If people can't keep up, they should just quit.
Hey, what's up? How's your day going?
Ugh, it's been trash. Just got out of a game with absolute noobs who have no idea what they're doing. Like, why even bother playing if you're gonna suck so bad?
Yikes, that sounds rough. I guess everyone has to start somewhere though, right? I just came on to unwind after work. How's the new update treating you?

The update's fine, but it’s useless when you get paired with brain-dead teammates. And don't even get me started on those annoying squeakers. It's like, mute your mics if you're not old enough to play.
